# .shopifyignore — files excluded from `shopify theme push` and `shopify theme dev`
#
# Strategy (R216 — production phase):
#   - Code files (sections/, snippets/, assets/, layout/, locales/,
#     config/settings_schema.json) are always pushed.
#   - Merchant-content files (templates/*.json, config/settings_data.json,
#     sections/*-group.json) are IGNORED on push to the live theme so code
#     revisions never wipe out merchant edits made in the theme editor.
#
# Why these specific files:
#   * templates/*.json — every page's section composition + per-section
#     settings (heading text, image refs, color pickers, etc.). When a
#     merchant edits via the theme editor, the JSON is rewritten with
#     their inputs. A `shopify theme push` from this codebase would
#     overwrite all of that with placeholder defaults.
#   * config/settings_data.json — global theme settings (active color
#     scheme, brand colours, fonts, social URLs, etc.). Merchant tunes
#     these in Theme Settings; a push from this codebase would reset
#     everything to the defaults declared in settings_schema.json.
#   * sections/*-group.json — header-group / footer-group composition,
#     announcement-banner copy, footer menu links, payment-icon toggle,
#     etc. Same overwrite risk as templates/*.json.
#
# Trade-off: `shopify theme dev` reads these from disk too — so the local
# dev preview shows placeholder content (the defaults committed in this
# repo) rather than what's on the live store. That's the right trade-off
# for our workflow: the dev preview is for code testing, the live store
# is for merchant content; the two stay independent.
#
# When you DO want to push a content-file change (e.g. adjusting a
# placeholder default for a fresh-install demo), bypass with --only:
#   shopify theme push --only "templates/index.json" --theme <ID>
# Or comment out the matching ignore line below, push, then restore.
#
# Theme Store-banned patterns below (.md files, docs/) MUST stay ignored —
# Shopify rejects uploads containing them.

# Merchant content — preserve live-theme edits across code pushes
templates/*.json
config/settings_data.json
sections/*-group.json

# Theme Store ban-list — never push any of these
*.md
docs/*
references/*
.github/*
.theme-check.yml
.editorconfig
.gitignore
.prettierrc*

# Dev-time theme-check config that Shopify's backend doesn't need
.shopifyrc.json

# Node / local dev artefacts
node_modules/*
*.log
.env
.env.*

# OS files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Editor backups
*.swp
*~
*.bak

# Local theme-package zip artefacts (output of `shopify theme package`).
# Pushing one in would create a nested-zip recursion in the live theme.
*.zip

# Local Claude Code agent state — never ship to storefront
.claude/*
.claude-code/*
